R. Brad Oates J.D.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 10:31 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Stone Advisors LP



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
R. Brad Oates J.D.Co-Managing Partner, Chief Strategy Officer, Advisor and Chairman, Stone Advisors LPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships63--
Background

		Mr. R. Brad Oates, J.D. serves as Co-Managing Partner, Chief Strategy Officer and Advisor of Stone Advisors LP. Mr. Oates founded Stone Advisors in January 2002. He was Managing Director and Operating Partner at Z capital Management LLC. Mr. Oates is integrated into the Investment Team and assists in the management and oversight of portfolio company initiatives including, but not limited to, the financial services industry. Prior to Stone Advisors LP, Mr. Oates held ... a successful career in the NFL with the St. Louis Cardinals, the Detroit Lions and the Green Bay Packers. He served as the President of the LexisNexis Risk Solutions Group, from May 2000 to March 2001 and served as its Chief Strategy Advisor for the LexisNexis Group until January 2002. From 1988 to 2003, he served as President and Chief Operating Officer of Bluebonnet Savings Bank FSB and its various subsidiaries where he successfully merged over $3 billion in assets across 150 systems and 1,000 employees and implemented aggressive cost control and asset/liability strategies that resulted in annual return on equity of approximately 30% during his tenure. He also served as Executive Vice President for Stone Holdings, Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at RiskWise International, LLC. In 1984, he retired from professional football and to become Senior Vice President and General Counsel and a Board Member of Stockton Savings Association and Troy & Nichols Mortgage Company. He served as Vice President at Stone Capital. He currently serves as Chairman of Stone Advisors LP. He serves as the Chairman of Universal Hardwood Flooring, I.I.I.P.; xTech; Stone Bank FSB; Integration Solutions, LLC and IntegriView, LLC. He serves as the Chairman of Stone Advisory Holdings, LLC and NFC Global, Inc. He served as the Chairman of eBureau, LLC. Since November 1996, Mr. Oates served as Vice Chairman of Bluebonnet Savings Bank. He has been a Director of Modere, Inc. since March 13, 2012. He serves as a Director of CIT Bank, National Association (CIT Bank, N.A.), GearingStone, LLC and Neways Inc. He has been an Independent Director of CIT Group Inc. since December 18, 2009. He served as Director of Bluebonnet Savings Bank. He served as a Director of CIT Holdings, LLC since December 22, 2009. He served as Director of eBureau, LLC. He served as Chairman and Director of the Texas Savings and Bankers Community Association. He served as Chairman of RiskWise International. This followed a successful collegiate academic and football career at Brigham Young University where he was Captain of the football team and earned All-conference young University's J. Redben Clark Law School. The same year, he was awarded the Professional Responsibility Award by the Utha Bar Foundation. He is the Author of the Seven Management Disciplines for Highly Successful Businesses, involving the management disciplines of (i) Strategy Management, (ii) Human Resources Management, (iii) Systems Management, (iv) Operations Management, (v) Customer Experience Management, (vi) Financial Management, and (vii) Risk Management. Mr. Oates received a J.D. from the J. Reuben Clark Law School at BYU with honors in the upper 20% of his class in 1982 and his undergraduate degree in Political Science from Brigham Young University (BYU) in 1976.Read Full Background




